Verifying the Active Processes
Once configured, you can launch the CLI using the gemini command. To ensure that your runtime hub has successfully spun up your subprocesses without throwing conflicts, you can use the built-in management command directly inside the prompt interface:

Plaintext
/mcp list
This will output a status checklist showing which subprocesses successfully bound to the terminal session, making the Gemini CLI a highly flexible option if you want to bring your custom monorepo tooling suite straight into your terminal workflow.

