This provides a local, graph-based knowledge storage system.

The Problem it Solves: AI agents suffer from amnesia between different context windows or when switching tabs.

How it works: When you tell the agent, "Remember that my local database project is called mysticDB and uses snake_case keys," the agent calls this server to save entities and relationships into a persistent JSON graph file on your system. Next week, in a completely fresh chat session, the agent automatically searches its graph and recalls your structural rules.

2. Sequential Thinking (@modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking)
This is an official reasoning orchestrator designed to stop agents from rushing into incorrect code fixes.

The Problem it Solves: Agents often hallucinate a solution, write a massive code block, realize it fails, and then recursively break more files trying to fix it.

How it works: It forces the agent to use a dynamic reasoning chain (process_thought). The agent must explicitly state its hypothesis, challenge its assumptions, track its steps, and synthesize an architecture before it is allowed to touch your workspace files.

